. The experiment is based on the crivit species, which exists in the Visitor's home planet.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.shelfari.com/books/5375268/V-The-Crivit-Experiment |title=V: The Crivit Experiment (V 8) by Allen L. Wold |publisher=Shelfari.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-17}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Episode list |EpisodeNumber=9\n |Title        = The New England Resistance\n |WrittenBy    = Tim Sullivan\n |AltDate      = June 1985\n |ProdCode     = {{ISBNT|0-523-42467-1}}\n |ShortSummary = A human scientist tries to test a toxin that he developed, and that could help decimate the Visitors. Tipped off by a human collaborator, the Visitors arrive in New England, desperate to destroy this new threat to their renewed invasion of Earth. The local Resistance is then picked off, and a new group of resistance fighters ends up being formed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.shelfari.com/books/205715/V-The-New-England-Resistance |title=V: The New England Resistance (V 9) by Tim Sullivan |publisher=Shelfari.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-17}}</ref>\n}}\n{{Episode list |EpisodeNumber=10\n |Title        = Death Tide\n |WrittenBy    = A.C. Crispin\n |AltDate      = July 1985\n |ProdCode     = {{ISBNT|0-523-42469-8}}\n |ShortSummary = The Resistance works on a new version of the red dust that lives in seaweed and thus protects the planet's water, while also trying to coax a strain to live in land-based vegetation; Diana works on a defoliant that will destroy the seaweed. Marjorie Donovan returns.\n}}\n{{Episode list |EpisodeNumber=11\n |Title        = The Texas Run\n |WrittenBy    = George W. Proctor\n |AltDate      = September 1985\n |ProdCode     = {{ISBNT|0-523-42470-1}}\n |ShortSummary = The Texas resistance has been weakened by Commander Garth and his batch of Shocktroopers. Set after the TV episode \"Visitors Choice\".\n}}\n{{Episode list |EpisodeNumber=12\n |Title        = Path to Conquest\n |WrittenBy    = Howard Weinstein\n |AltDate      = September 1987\n |ProdCode     = {{ISBNT