e]] {{small|(3,5)}}\n;Additional personnel\n*[[Mark Charig]] \u2013 [[cornet]] {{small|(2)}}\n*Robin Miller \u2013 [[oboe]] {{small|(2)}}\n*[[George Chkiantz]] \u2013 recording, [[Audio engineer|engineering]]\n*Rod Thear \u2013 recording, assistant engineering\n*Chris, Tex, Harvey and Peter Walmsley \u2013 equipment\n*[[John Kosh]] \u2013 [[Album cover|cover]]\n*[[Gered Mankowitz]] \u2013 [[photography]]\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (1974)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{Album chart | Billboard200 | 66 | artist = King Crimson | accessdate = 14 November 2017 | refname = \"US Billboard 200\"}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* {{cite book|last=Macon|first=Edward&nbsp;L.|year=1997|title=Rocking the classics: English progressive&nbsp;rock and the counterculture|location=Oxford and New&nbsp;York|publisher=Oxford University|isbn=0-19-509887-0 |url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/rockingclassicse0000maca}}\n* {{Cite book |title=Robert&nbsp;Fripp: From crimson&nbsp;king to crafty&nbsp;master  |first=Eric  |last=Tamm  |url=http://www.progressiveears.com/frippbook/ch10.htm  |year=2003  |origyear=1990  |publisher=Faber and Faber (1990)  |isbn=0-571-16289-4  |edition=Progressive Ears  |id=[http://www.erictamm.com/rf.zip  Zipped Microsoft Word Document] |accessdate=25 March 2012  |url-status=dead  |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111026180438/http://www.progressiveears.com/frippbook/ch10.htm  |archivedate=26 October 2011}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* [[Andrew Keeling|Keeling, Andrew]] (2007). [http://www.songsouponsea.com/Keeling/Keeling-Red.html King Crimson: Red: An Analysis by Andrew Keeling].\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Discogs master|463|Red}}\n\n{{King Crimson}}\n\n[[Category:King Crimson albums]]\n[[Category:1974 albums]]\n[[Category:Island Records albums]]\n[[Category:Atlantic Records albums]]\n[[Category:Polydor Records albums]]\n[[Category:E.G. 