 \u2013 [[drums]] (1-5, 7), [[slit drum]] (6-7)\n\n'''Technical'''\n*[[Rhett Davies]] \u2013 production\n*Nigel Mills \u2013 assistant [[Audio engineer|engineer]]\n*Graham Davies \u2013 gear\n*[[Peter Saville (graphic designer)|Peter Saville]] \u2013 graphic design\n*John Kyrk \u2013 [[knot]]work<ref>{{cite web|url=http://et.stok.ca/articles/562-8.html|title=\"Discipline\" Celtic Knotwork|date=22 December 1998|website=et.stok.ca|access-date=29 June 2019}}</ref> (uncredited; 1981, 1986 and 1989 issues only)\n*Steve Ball \u2013 knotwork (2001 issue onwards)\n*Paddy Spinks \u2013 [[Talent manager#Music managers|strategic management]]\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (1981)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{Album chart | Billboard200 | 45 | artist = King Crimson  | accessdate = 14 November 2017 | refname = \"US Billboard 200\"}}\n|-\n{{Album chart | UK | 41 | artist = King Crimson | date = 1981-10-10 | accessdate = 14 November 2017 | refname = \"UK chart\"}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n\n* {{Discogs master|577|Discipline}}\n*[http://www.elephant-talk.com/wiki/Discipline Wiki with song lyrics] at fan-site  Elephant Talk (inspired by ''Discipline'''s \"[[Elephant Talk]]\")\n\n{{King Crimson}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Discipline (King Crimson Album)}}\n[[Category:1981 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Rhett Davies]]\n[[Category:King Crimson albums]]\n[[Category:E.G. Records albums]]\n[[Category:Virgin Records albums]]\n[[Category:Warner Records albums]]\n[[Category:New wave albums by English artists]]\n", "name_user": "95.150.171.86", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Discipline_(King_Crimson_album)"}
{"title_page": "To Our Children's Children's Children", "text_new": "{{Use British English|date=July 2011}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2011}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = To Our Children's Children's Children\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[The Moody Blues]]\n| cover      = childrenschildrenschildren.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = 21 November 1969\n| recorded   = May\u2013September 1969 at [[Decca Studios]], [[West Hampstead]], London, England\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Progressive rock]], [[Psychedelic rock]]\n| length     = 40:15\n| label      = [[Threshold Records|Threshold]]\n| producer   = [[Tony Clarke (record producer)|Tony Clarke]]\n| prev_title = [[On the Threshold of a Dream]]\n| prev_year  = 1969\n| next_title = [[A Question of Balance]]\n| next_year  = 1970\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = To Our Children's Children's Children\n | type        = Studio\n | single1     = [[Watching and Waiting]]\n | single1date = 31 October 1969\n}}\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n|rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n|rev1score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref>{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r838005}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''To Our Children's Children's Children''''' is the fifth album by [[The Moody Blues]], released in November 1969.\n\n\"[[Watching and Waiting]]\" was released as a [[single (music)|single]] to promote the album, but sold poorly.  On the other hand, \"[[Gypsy (Of a Strange and Distant Time)]]\" became a fan and [[album oriented rock]] radio favorite, despite never being released as a single, and remained in the band's concert setlist through the 1970s.\n\n==Background==\nThe album was the first released on the group's newly formed [[Threshold Records|Threshold]] record label, which was named after the band's previous album from the same year, ''[[On the Threshold of a Dream]]''. It was inspired by the [[Apollo 11|1969 moon landing]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://player.bfi.org.uk/free/film/watch-to-our-childrens-childrens-children-1969-online|title=Watch To Our Children's Children's Children - BFI Player|website=BFI Player|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref> In the opening track, \"[[Higher and Higher (Moody Blues song)|Higher and Higher]]\", sound effects of a rocket launching begin the song and last for the first minute.\n\n==Release==\nWhile the extracted [[single (music)|single]], \"[[Watching and Waiting]],\" did not do well in that market, ''To Our Children's Children's Children'' was critically well-received and sold well, reaching number 2 in the UK albums chart<ref name=\"UK chart\">{{cite web |url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/11532/moody-blues/ |title=Moody Blues <nowiki>| Full Official Chart History |</nowiki> Official Charts Company |website=[[Official Charts Company|Official Charts]] |accessdate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> and number 14 in the US.<ref name=\"US chart\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/300750/the-moody-blues/chart?f=305 |title=The Moody Blues \u2013 Chart History <nowiki>|</nowiki> Billboard |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> The album was mixed and released in both [[Stereophonic sound|stereo]] and [[quadraphonic sound|quadraphonic]].\n\nThe album was one of those listened to, on [[Compact Cassette|cassette tape]], by the crew of [[Apollo 15]] in 1971.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=fNBp1kaLhEkC&pg=PA91|title=HSA Space Exploration and Aviation Auction Catalog #6000|date=1 February 2008|publisher=Heritage Capital Corporation|accessdate=13 January 2018|via=Google Books}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{track listing\n| headline        = Side A\n| extra_column    = Lead vocals\n| title1          = [[Higher and Higher (The Moody Blues song)|Higher and Higher]]\n| writer1         = [[Graeme Edge]]\n| extra1          = Pinder (narration)\n| length1         = 4:07\n| title2          = Eyes of a Child I\n| writer2         = [[John Lodge (musician)|John Lodge]]\n| extra2          = Lodge\n| length2         = 3:24\n| title3          = [[Floating (The Moody Blues song)|Floating]]\n| writer3         = [[Ray Thomas]]\n| extra3          = Thomas\n| length3         = 3:02\n| title4          = Eyes of a Child II\n| writer4         = Lodge\n| extra4          = Lodge\n| length4         = 1:20\n| title5          = I Never Thought I'd Live to Be a Hundred\n| writer5         = [[Justin Hayward]]\n| extra5          = Hayward\n| length5         = 1:05\n| title6          = [[Beyond (song)|Beyond]]\n| writer6         = Edge\n| extra6          = ''instrumental''\n| length6         = 2:59\n| title7          = [[Out and In]]\n| writer7         = [[Mike Pinder]], Lodge\n| extra7          = Pinder\n| length7         = 3:50\n}}\n{{track listing\n| headline        = Side B\n| extra_column    = Lead vocals\n| title1          = [[Gypsy (Of a Strange and Distant Time)]]\n| writer1         = Hayward\n| extra1          = Hayward\n| length1         = 3:33\n| title2          = [[Eternity Road (song)|Eternity Road]]\n| writer2         = Thomas\n| extra2          = Thomas\n| length2         = 4:19\n| title3          = [[Candle of Life]]\n| writer3         = Lodge\n| extra3          = Lodge, Hayward\n| length3         = 4:15\n| title4          = [[Sun Is Still Shining]]\n| writer4         = Pinder\n| extra4          = Pinder\n| length4         = 3:40\n| title5          = I Never Thought I'd Live to Be a Million\n| writer5         = Hayward\n| extra5          = Hayward\n| length5         = 0:34\n| title6          = [[Watching and Waiting]]\n| writer6         = Hayward, Thomas\n| extra6          = Hayward\n| length6         = 4:16\n}}\n\nIn March 2006, the album was remastered into [[Super Audio CD|SACD]] and repackaged into a 2CD Deluxe Edition.\n\n{{track listing\n| collapsed       = yes\n| headline        = 2006 SACD Deluxe Edition bonus disc\n| title1          = Gypsy\n| note1           = Alternate version\n| writer1         = Hayward\n| length1         = 4:17\n\n| title2 = Candle of Life\n| note2 = Alternate version\n| writer2 = Lodge\n| length2 = 4:59\n\n| title3 = Sun Is Still Shining\n| note3 = Extended version\n| writer3 = Pinder\n| length3 = 4:07\n\n| title4 = Gypsy\n| note4 = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer4 = Hayward\n| length4 = 3:21\n\n| title5 = Sunset\n| note5 = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer5 = Pinder\n| length5 = 3:54\n\n| title6 = Never Comes the Day\n| note6 = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer6 = Hayward\n| length6 = 4:42\n\n| title7 = Are You Sitting Comfortably\n| note7 = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer7 = Hayward, Thomas\n| length7 = 2:54\n\n| title8 = The Dream\n| note8 = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer8 = Edge\n| length8 = 0:58\n\n| title9 = Have You Heard Pt. 1/The Voyage/Have You Heard Pt. 2\n| note9 = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer9 = Pinder\n| length9 = 5:42\n\n| title10 = [[Nights in White Satin]]\n| note10 = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer10 = Hayward\n| length10 = 3:12\n\n| title11 = [[Legend of a Mind]]\n| note11 = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer11 = Thomas\n| length11 = 4:37\n}}\n\nIn 2008, a remaster for single standard audio CD was issued with the five bonus tracks.\n\n{{track listing\n| collapsed        = yes\n| headline         = 2008 Single Standard CD Remaster tracks\n| title14          = Gypsy\n| note14           = Alternate version\n| writer14         = Hayward\n| length14         = 4:16\n| title15          = Candle of Life\n| note15           = Alternate version\n| writer15         = Lodge\n| length15         = 4:55\n| title16          = Sun Is Still Shining\n| note16           = Extended version\n| writer16         = Pinder\n| length16         = 4:03\n| title17          = Have You Heard Pt. 1/The Voyage/Have You Heard Pt. 2\n| note17           = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer17         = Pinder\n| length17         = 5:36\n| title18          = Legend of a Mind\n| note18           = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer18         = Thomas\n| length18         = 4:33\n}}\n\n==Chart positions==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Chart\n!Position\n|-\n|1969\n|[[UK Albums Chart]]\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|1970\n|[[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]\n|align=\"center\"|14\n|}\n\n==Personnel==\n*[[Justin Hayward]] \u2013 vocals, guitars, [[sitar]]\n*[[John Lodge (musician)|John Lodge]] \u2013 vocals, bass guitar, harp, acoustic guitar{{citation needed|date=April 2015}}\n*[[Ray Thomas]] \u2013 vocals, flute, tambourine, [[bass flute]], [[oboe]]\n*[[Graeme Edge]] \u2013 drums, percussion\n*[[Mike Pinder]] \u2013 vocals, [[Mellotron]], piano, [[EMS VCS 3]], [[Hammond organ]], acoustic guitar, [[celesta]], [[double bass]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Discogs master|41331}}\n\n{{Moody Blues}}\n\n[[Category:The Moody Blues albums]]\n[[Category:1969 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Tony Clarke (record producer)]]\n[[Category:Threshold Records albums]]\n[[Category:Outer space themed songs|*]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use British English|date=July 2011}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2011}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = To Our Children's Children's Children\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[The Moody Blues]]\n| cover      = childrenschildrenschildren.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = 21 November 1969\n| recorded   = May\u2013September 1969 at [[Decca Studios]], [[West Hampstead]], London, England\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Progressive rock]]\n| length     = 40:15\n| label      = [[Threshold Records|Threshold]]\n| producer   = [[Tony Clarke (record producer)|Tony Clarke]]\n| prev_title = [[On the Threshold of a Dream]]\n| prev_year  = 1969\n| next_title = [[A Question of Balance]]\n| next_year  = 1970\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = To Our Children's Children's Children\n | type        = Studio\n | single1     = [[Watching and Waiting]]\n | single1date = 31 October 1969\n}}\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n|rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n|rev1score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref>{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r838005}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''To Our Children's Children's Children''''' is the fifth album by [[The Moody Blues]], released in November 1969.\n\n\"[[Watching and Waiting]]\" was released as a [[single (music)|single]] to promote the album, but sold poorly.  On the other hand, \"[[Gypsy (Of a Strange and Distant Time)]]\" became a fan and [[album oriented rock]] radio favorite, despite never being released as a single, and remained in the band's concert setlist through the 1970s.\n\n==Background==\nThe album was the first released on the group's newly formed [[Threshold Records|Threshold]] record label, which was named after the band's previous album from the same year, ''[[On the Threshold of a Dream]]''. It was inspired by the [[Apollo 11|1969 moon landing]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://player.bfi.org.uk/free/film/watch-to-our-childrens-childrens-children-1969-online|title=Watch To Our Children's Children's Children - BFI Player|website=BFI Player|accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref> In the opening track, \"[[Higher and Higher (Moody Blues song)|Higher and Higher]]\", sound effects of a rocket launching begin the song and last for the first minute.\n\n==Release==\nWhile the extracted [[single (music)|single]], \"[[Watching and Waiting]],\" did not do well in that market, ''To Our Children's Children's Children'' was critically well-received and sold well, reaching number 2 in the UK albums chart<ref name=\"UK chart\">{{cite web |url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/11532/moody-blues/ |title=Moody Blues <nowiki>| Full Official Chart History |</nowiki> Official Charts Company |website=[[Official Charts Company|Official Charts]] |accessdate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> and number 14 in the US.<ref name=\"US chart\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/300750/the-moody-blues/chart?f=305 |title=The Moody Blues \u2013 Chart History <nowiki>|</nowiki> Billboard |website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=June 12, 2016}}</ref> The album was mixed and released in both [[Stereophonic sound|stereo]] and [[quadraphonic sound|quadraphonic]].\n\nThe album was one of those listened to, on [[Compact Cassette|cassette tape]], by the crew of [[Apollo 15]] in 1971.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=fNBp1kaLhEkC&pg=PA91|title=HSA Space Exploration and Aviation Auction Catalog #6000|date=1 February 2008|publisher=Heritage Capital Corporation|accessdate=13 January 2018|via=Google Books}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{track listing\n| headline        = Side A\n| extra_column    = Lead vocals\n| title1          = [[Higher and Higher (The Moody Blues song)|Higher and Higher]]\n| writer1         = [[Graeme Edge]]\n| extra1          = Pinder (narration)\n| length1         = 4:07\n| title2          = Eyes of a Child I\n| writer2         = [[John Lodge (musician)|John Lodge]]\n| extra2          = Lodge\n| length2         = 3:24\n| title3          = [[Floating (The Moody Blues song)|Floating]]\n| writer3         = [[Ray Thomas]]\n| extra3          = Thomas\n| length3         = 3:02\n| title4          = Eyes of a Child II\n| writer4         = Lodge\n| extra4          = Lodge\n| length4         = 1:20\n| title5          = I Never Thought I'd Live to Be a Hundred\n| writer5         = [[Justin Hayward]]\n| extra5          = Hayward\n| length5         = 1:05\n| title6          = [[Beyond (song)|Beyond]]\n| writer6         = Edge\n| extra6          = ''instrumental''\n| length6         = 2:59\n| title7          = [[Out and In]]\n| writer7         = [[Mike Pinder]], Lodge\n| extra7          = Pinder\n| length7         = 3:50\n}}\n{{track listing\n| headline        = Side B\n| extra_column    = Lead vocals\n| title1          = [[Gypsy (Of a Strange and Distant Time)]]\n| writer1         = Hayward\n| extra1          = Hayward\n| length1         = 3:33\n| title2          = [[Eternity Road (song)|Eternity Road]]\n| writer2         = Thomas\n| extra2          = Thomas\n| length2         = 4:19\n| title3          = [[Candle of Life]]\n| writer3         = Lodge\n| extra3          = Lodge, Hayward\n| length3         = 4:15\n| title4          = [[Sun Is Still Shining]]\n| writer4         = Pinder\n| extra4          = Pinder\n| length4         = 3:40\n| title5          = I Never Thought I'd Live to Be a Million\n| writer5         = Hayward\n| extra5          = Hayward\n| length5         = 0:34\n| title6          = [[Watching and Waiting]]\n| writer6         = Hayward, Thomas\n| extra6          = Hayward\n| length6         = 4:16\n}}\n\nIn March 2006, the album was remastered into [[Super Audio CD|SACD]] and repackaged into a 2CD Deluxe Edition.\n\n{{track listing\n| collapsed       = yes\n| headline        = 2006 SACD Deluxe Edition bonus disc\n| title1          = Gypsy\n| note1           = Alternate version\n| writer1         = Hayward\n| length1         = 4:17\n\n| title2 = Candle of Life\n| note2 = Alternate version\n| writer2 = Lodge\n| length2 = 4:59\n\n| title3 = Sun Is Still Shining\n| note3 = Extended version\n| writer3 = Pinder\n| length3 = 4:07\n\n| title4 = Gypsy\n| note4 = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer4 = Hayward\n| length4 = 3:21\n\n| title5 = Sunset\n| note5 = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer5 = Pinder\n| length5 = 3:54\n\n| title6 = Never Comes the Day\n| note6 = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer6 = Hayward\n| length6 = 4:42\n\n| title7 = Are You Sitting Comfortably\n| note7 = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer7 = Hayward, Thomas\n| length7 = 2:54\n\n| title8 = The Dream\n| note8 = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer8 = Edge\n| length8 = 0:58\n\n| title9 = Have You Heard Pt. 1/The Voyage/Have You Heard Pt. 2\n| note9 = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer9 = Pinder\n| length9 = 5:42\n\n| title10 = [[Nights in White Satin]]\n| note10 = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer10 = Hayward\n| length10 = 3:12\n\n| title11 = [[Legend of a Mind]]\n| note11 = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer11 = Thomas\n| length11 = 4:37\n}}\n\nIn 2008, a remaster for single standard audio CD was issued with the five bonus tracks.\n\n{{track listing\n| collapsed        = yes\n| headline         = 2008 Single Standard CD Remaster tracks\n| title14          = Gypsy\n| note14           = Alternate version\n| writer14         = Hayward\n| length14         = 4:16\n| title15          = Candle of Life\n| note15           = Alternate version\n| writer15         = Lodge\n| length15         = 4:55\n| title16          = Sun Is Still Shining\n| note16           = Extended version\n| writer16         = Pinder\n| length16         = 4:03\n| title17          = Have You Heard Pt. 1/The Voyage/Have You Heard Pt. 2\n| note17           = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer17         = Pinder\n| length17         = 5:36\n| title18          = Legend of a Mind\n| note18           = BBC radio concert 17 December 1969\n| writer18         = Thomas\n| length18         = 4:33\n}}\n\n==Chart positions==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Chart\n!Position\n|-\n|1969\n|[[UK Albums Chart]]\n|align=\"center\"|2\n|-\n|1970\n|[[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]\n|align=\"center\"|14\n|}\n\n==Personnel==\n*[[Justin Hayward]] \u2013 vocals, guitars, [[sitar]]\n*[[John Lodge (musician)|John Lodge]] \u2013 vocals, bass guitar, harp, acoustic guitar{{citation needed|date=April 2015}}\n*[[Ray Thomas]] \u2013 vocals, flute, tambourine, [[bass flute]], [[oboe]]\n*[[Graeme Edge]] \u2013 drums, percussion\n*[[Mike Pinder]] \u2013 vocals, [[Mellotron]], piano, [[EMS VCS 3]], [[Hammond organ]], acoustic guitar, [[celesta]], [[double bass]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Discogs master|41331}}\n\n{{Moody Blues}}\n\n[[Category:The Moody Blues albums]]\n[[Category:1969 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Tony Clarke (record producer)]]\n[[Category:Threshold Records albums]]\n[[Category:Outer space themed songs|*]]\n", "name_user": "95.150.171.86", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/To_Our_Children%27s_Children%27s_Children"}
{"title_page": "List of California county jails", "text_new": "California's county jails function like [[county jails]] throughout the United States: they are used to incarcerated people [[pre-trial detention|pre-trial]], through a [[trial]] and [[sentencing]], and for some sentences of commitment. The majority of people incarcerated in California's county jails have not been sentenced (they are pre-trial and have not been convicted of a crime).\n\nHistorically, time would be served in a county jail for sentences of less than a year, including sentences for [[misdemeanors]] and some [[felonies]]. In 2011, the [[Public Safety Realignment initiative|Public Safety Realignment Act]] was signed into law in response to the Supreme Court case [[Brown v. Plata]] and the resulting court order to address prison overcrowding in the state. Realignment \"shifted responsibility for all sentenced non-violent, non-serious, non-sex offenders from state to local jurisdictions\"<ref>{{cite web |author=Board of State and Community Corrections |title=Realignment |url=http://www.bscc.ca.gov/m_realignment/ |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419054253/http://www.bscc.ca.gov/m_realignment/ |archive-date=2020-04-18 |publisher=Board of State and Community Corrections}}</ref>, which decreased California prison populations, increased California county jail populations, and changed the types and distribution of crimes for which people were serving sentences in county jails.\n\nFor comparison, in December 2019 there were approximately 71,200 people incarcerated in California county jails (based on average daily population)<ref>{{cite web |author=Board of State and Community Corrections |title=Jail Profile Survey Query |url=https://app.bscc.ca.gov/joq//jps/QuerySelection.asp |archiveurl=https://archive.org/details/california-jail-population-data-dec-2019 |archive-date=2020-04-18 |publisher=Board of State and Community Corrections}}</ref>, 124,027 people incarcerated in California state prisons<ref>{{cite web |author=California Department of Corrections and Rehabilitation |title=Monthly Total Population Report |url=https://www.cdcr.ca.gov/research/wp-content/uploads/sites/174/2020/01/Tpop1d1912.pdf |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419050413/https://www.cdcr.ca.gov/research/wp-content/uploads/sites/174/2020/01/Tpop1d1912.pdf |archive-date=2020-04-18 |publisher=California Department of Corrections and Rehabilitatio}}</ref>, and 51,923 people on parole in California<ref>{{cite web |author=California Department of Corrections and Rehabilitation |title=Monthly Total Population Report |url=https://www.cdcr.ca.gov/research/wp-content/uploads/sites/174/2020/01/Tpop1d1912.pdf |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200419050413/https://www.cdcr.ca.gov/research/wp-content/uploads/sites/174/2020/01/Tpop1d1912.pdf |archive-date=2020-04-18 |publisher=California Department of Corrections and Rehabilitatio}}</ref>.\n\n[[File:Fresno County Jail taken from County of Fresno.jpg|thumb|Fresno County Jail]]\n[[File:Los Angeles Men&#039;s Central Jail 2.jpg|thumb|Los Angeles Men's Central Jail 2]]\n[[File:Los Angeles County Jail &quot;Twin Towers Correctional Facility&quot;.jpg|thumb|Los Angeles Twin Towers Facility]]\n[[File:Monterey Co Jail.jpg|thumb|Monterey County Jail]]\n[[Image:hallofjustice.jpg|thumb|right|200px|The San Francisco Hall of Justice Complex, including County Jail #4]]\n\n==California county jails==\n\nRated capacity and average daily population reports from the [[California Board of State and Community Corrections]] were used to determine what constitutes a distinct jail facility for this list.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Jail \n! County\n! Rated Capacity<ref>{{cite web |author=Board of State and Community Corrections |title=Rated Capacities of Type II, III, & IV Local Adult Detention Facilities (Dec 2006 \u2013 Dec 2019; last update 1/9/20) |url=http://www.bscc.ca.gov/s_fsojailprofilesurvey/ |archiveurl=https://archive.org/details/rc-of-type-ii-iii-iv-local-adult-detention-facilities-dec-2006-dec-2019-for-web |archive-date=2020-04-18 |publisher=Board of State and Community Corrections}}</ref>\n! Average Daily Population (ADP)<ref>{{cite web |author=Board of State and Community Corrections |title=Jail Profile Survey Query |url=https://app.bscc.ca.gov/joq//jps/QuerySelection.asp |archiveurl=https://archive.org/details/query-result |archive-date=2020-04-18 |publisher=Board of State and Community Corrections}}</ref>\n! Notes\n|-\n| [[Santa Rita Jail]]<ref>{{cite web |author=Alameda County Sheriff's Office |title=Santa Rita Jail |url=https://www.alamedacountysheriff.org/dc_srj.php |publisher=Alameda County Sheriff's Office}}</ref>\n| [[Alameda County, California|Alameda]]\n| 3489\n| 2563\n|\n|-\n| [[Amador County Jail]]<ref>{{cite web |author=Amador County Sheriff's Office |title=Amador County Jail |url=https://www.amadorsheriff.org/corrections-div/amador-jail |publisher=Amador County Sheriff's Office}}</ref>\n| [[Amador County, California|Amador]]\n| 76\n| 94\n|\n|-\n| [[Butte County Jail]]<ref>{{cite web |author=Butte County Sheriff's Office |title=Butte County Jail |url=https://www.buttecounty.net/sheriffcoroner/jailinfo |publisher=Butte County Sheriff's Office}}</ref>\n| [[Butte County, California|Butte]]\n| 614\n| 538\n|\n|-\n| [[Calaveras County Adult Detention Facility]]<ref>{{cite web |author=Calaveras County Sheriff's Office |title=Calaveras County Adult Detention Facility |url=https://sheriff.calaverasgov.us/Detention-Facility |publisher=Calaveras County Sheriff's Office}}</ref>\n| [[Calaveras County, California|Calaveras]]\n| 128\n| 100\n|\n|-\n| [[Colusa County Jail]]<ref>{{cite web |author=Colusa County Sheriff's Office |title=Colusa County Jail |url=https://www.countyofcolusa.org/158/Jail |publisher=Colusa County Sheriff's Office}}</ref>\n| [[Colusa County, California|Colusa]]\n| 92\n| 59\n|\n|-\n| [[Marsh Creek Detention Facility]]<ref>{{cite web |author=Contra Costa County Sheriff's Office |title=Marsh Creek Detention Facility |url=http://www.cocosheriff.org/bureaus/custody_services/marsh_creek.htm |publisher=Contra Costa County Sheriff's Office}}</ref>\n| [[Contra Costa County, California|Contra Costa]]\n| 188\n| 49\n|\n|-\n| [[Martinez Detention Facility]]<ref>{{cite web |author=Contra Costa County Sheriff's Office |title=Martinez Detention Facility |url=http://www.cocosheriff.org/bureaus/custody_services/martinez_detention.htm |publisher=Contra Costa County Sheriff's Office}}</ref>\n| [[Contra Costa County, California|Contra Costa]]\n| 695\n| 418\n|\n|-\n| [[West County Detention Facility]]<ref>{{cite web |author=Contra Costa County Sheriff's Office |title=West County Detention Facility |url=http://www.cocosheriff.org/bureaus/custody_services/west_county.htm |publisher=Contra Costa County Sheriff's Office}}</ref>\n| [[Contra Costa County, California|Contra Costa]]\n| 1104\n| 628\n|\n|-\n| [[Del Norte County Jail]]<ref>{{cite web |author=Del Norte County Sheriff's Office |title=Del Norte County Sheriff's Office |url=http://www.co.del-norte.ca.us/departments/sheriff-department |publisher=Del Norte County Sheriff's Office}}</ref>\n| [[Del Norte County, California|Del Norte]]\n| 146\n| 104\n|\n|-\n| [[El Dorado County Jail, Placerville]]<ref>{{cite web |author=El Dorado County Sheriff's Office |title=El Dorado County Sheriff's Office |url=https://www.edcgov.us/Government/sheriff/Jail |publisher=El Dorado County Sheriff's Office}}</ref>\n| [[El Dorado County, California|El Dorado]]\n| 303\n| 243\n|\n|-\n| [[El Dorado County Jail, South Lake Tahoe]]<ref>{{cite web |author=El Dorado County Sheriff's Office |title=El Dorado County Sheriff's Office |url=https://www.edcgov.us/Government/sheriff/Jail |publisher=El Dorado County Sheriff's Office}}</ref>\n| [[El Dorado County, California|El Dorado]]\n| 158\n| 140\n|\n|-\n| [[Fresno County Jail#Main_Jail|Fresno County Main Jail]]<ref>{{cite web |author=Fresno County Sheriff's Office |title=Fresno Co